bcl:definition.bcl:text:
BC Housing means the British Columbia Housing Management Commission as
continued under section 10 (1) (b) of the Ministry of Lands, Parks and
  Housing Act;

emergency shelter means a building or a portion of a building that is
used to provide temporary accommodation free of charge to persons to meet the persons'
immediate basic needs for shelter;

person at risk means a person assessed to be a person at risk under
  section
  5;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
any prescribed designated policing unit that has been prescribed by the minister
            responsible for the Police Act as a police force under
            that Act;

the person, in the opinion of the police officer, is suffering physical harm or
            is at risk of suffering physical harm because of the extreme weather
            conditions;
